### Runtime

Default ports:
- public HTTP: `8080`
{% if grpc_enabled %}
- gRPC: `9090`
{% endif %}
- admin/docs HTTP: `8081`

Docs/admin endpoints:
- `GET /docs`
- `GET /swagger.json`
- `GET /openapi/swagger.json`

{% if http_enabled %}
HTTP endpoints:
- `GET /healthz`
- `GET /readyz`
- `GET /v1/ping`

{% endif %}
{% if grpc_enabled %}
gRPC API:
- `PingService/Ping`

Gateway path (for docs Try-it-out):
- `POST /v1/ping`

{% endif %}
### Architecture

- `cmd/{{ service_name }}` — composition root and lifecycle
- `internal/app` — transport adapters and interceptors
- `internal/pkg/model` — domain models and domain errors
- `internal/pkg/service` — business logic
- `internal/pkg/repository` — PostgreSQL adapters (when enabled)
- `internal/pkg/infrastructure` — Kafka adapters
- `internal/pb/{{ module_path }}/...` — generated proto/gateway/openapi files
- `test/mock` — generated mocks

### Error Handling

Domain errors map to transport statuses via one shared mapper:
- `ErrNotFound` -> gRPC `NotFound` / HTTP `404`
- `ErrInvalidArgument` -> gRPC `InvalidArgument` / HTTP `400`

When gRPC is enabled, interceptor adds `ErrorInfo.Reason` for known domain errors.

